<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[227,372,516,542]" box="[227,372,516,542]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,516,542]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="82" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,516,542]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[226,1437,566,785]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,566,592]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30458.1 is a phragmocone fragment with about 
<quantity box="[1012,1098,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="82" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
conch diameter; it is partly embedded in a haematite nodule (
<figureCitation box="[631,739,605,631]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[299,1373,1591,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-332@14.[291,1373,1587,1928]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 10. Stroboceras mane sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset, holotype MB.C.30458.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Ventral and lateral views. B. Cross section. C. Suture line, at ww =9.9 mm, wh=5.5 mm. Scale" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885220/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
) and was sectioned for the study of the whorl profile. The conch is discoidal and evolute (ww/dm=0.51; uw/dm= 0.45). The whorl profile is rounded-trapezoidal with almost flat venter separated from the convex flanks by an angular ventrolateral shoulder. Next to this shoulder is a shallow, wide longitudinal groove (
<figureCitation box="[838,945,720,746]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[299,1373,1591,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-332@14.[291,1373,1587,1928]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 10. Stroboceras mane sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset, holotype MB.C.30458.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Ventral and lateral views. B. Cross section. C. Suture line, at ww =9.9 mm, wh=5.5 mm. Scale" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885220/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
). The whorls apparently do not touch each other, but this may be caused by dissolution of the shell wall.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[227,1436,827,930]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">
The suture line has a very broad external lobe, an angular ventrolateral saddle in the area of the ventrolateral shoulder and a flat, somewhat undulating lateral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1168,865,891]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[227,270,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[299,1373,1591,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-332@14.[291,1373,1587,1928]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 10. Stroboceras mane sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset, holotype MB.C.30458.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Ventral and lateral views. B. Cross section. C. Suture line, at ww =9.9 mm, wh=5.5 mm. Scale" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885220/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). The siphuncle has a subcentral position.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[227,341,972,998]" box="[227,341,972,998]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,972,998]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="82" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,972,998]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[225,1436,1022,1125]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,437,1022,1048]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroboceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="15" pageNumber="82" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mane" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,437,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="82">Stroboceras mane</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[442,531,1023,1049]" pageId="15" pageNumber="82" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is an ancestral species of the genus and differs from almost all other species by the non-embracing whorls. Another distinguishing criterion is the very weak formation of longitudinal ridges and grooves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
